f\left(\frac{1}{2}\right) = \sqrt{\left(\frac{1}{2}\right)^2+1} + \sqrt{\left(1-\frac{1}{2}\right)^2+1} = \sqrt{\frac{5}{4}} + \sqrt{\frac{5}{4}} = \frac{1}{2}\sqrt{5} + \frac{1}{2}\sqrt{5} = \sqrt{5}.
